077c51d3d\",\"context_id\":null,\"scan_type\":\"observability_scout\",\"category\":\"maintenance\",\"title\":\"Classified error handling in trigger firing\",\"description\":\"In fireDueEntries (triggerScheduler.ts:250-306), all errors are caught uniformly with a single logger.error. Classify errors into categories: config_error (bad cron/parsedConfig), db_error (tenant DB failures), and orphan_trigger (persona deleted/disabled, already partially handled at lines 264-269 as warns). Add an error_class field to the log context and increment separate counters per class in SchedulerMetrics.\",\"reasoning\":\"A config error (bad cron expression) and a DB error (disk full) require completely different responses but currently look identical in logs. Error classification enables operators to set distinct alert thresholds � a spike in db_errors pages oncall immediately, while config_errors route to the team queue. This also surfaces chronic misconfigurations that silently waste scheduler cycles.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":3,\"impact\":6,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:30:11.828Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:30:11.828Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":2,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
